Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Mince @garlic{2%clove}. In a #medium bowl{}, combine @yogurt{4%tablespoon}, half the garlic, half the @Shawarma Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, 1 TBSP @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{1%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; add to bowl and turn to coat. Set aside to marinate.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil and 2 tsp salt.

Trim and dice @zucchini{1}(diced into ½-inch pieces). Dice @roma tomato{1}(diced into 1-inch pieces). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Quarter @lemon{1}. In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and remaining garlic to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Toss zucchini and tomato on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, remaining Shawarma Spice, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until veggies are browned and tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium heat. Remove chicken from marinade; allow excess to drip off. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}. Once cool enough to handle, slice crosswise.

> Medium heat is key in preventing the marinade from burning. If chicken begins to brown too quickly, lower the heat.

While chicken cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook until slightly softened, ~{1%minute}. Add @chicken stock concentrate{1}, ¾ cup water, ¼ tsp @turmeric{1%teaspoon}, 1 TBSP @butter{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Once boiling, stir in @couscous{½%cup}; cover pot and remove from heat. Let stand until water has absorbed and couscous is tender, at least ~{5%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use 1 1/2 cups water, ½ tsp turmeric, and 2 TBSP butter.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper. Toss roasted veggies with a big squeeze of lemon juice. Divide couscous and veggies between #bowls{2}; top with chicken and dollop with @hummus{4%tablespoon}. Drizzle with white sauce and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste. Sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.